%global packname  surveyoutliers
%global packver   0.1
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.1
Release:          1%{?dist}
Summary:          Helps Manage Outliers in Sample Surveys

License:          GPL-2 | GPL-3
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch
BuildRequires:    R-stats 
Requires:         R-stats 

%description
At present, the only functionality is the calculation of optimal one-sided
winsorizing cutoffs. The main function is optimal.onesided.cutoff.bygroup.
It calculates the optimal tuning parameter for one-sided winsorisation,
and so calculates winsorised values for a variable of interest. See the
help file for this function for more details and an example.

